You have heard wrong, this is simply impossible. Well maybe the mage you heard that from never trained in meditate, maybe he forgot to sit, but otherwise, it's impossible. Any class sitting will regen 5k+ mana in 20 min, and if you have a 5k manapool, you most likely have some mana regen AAs, FT items, etc. Or you can simply cannipet to get fm in a few minutes.<br>
<br>
***<br>
Not to be mentioning they get MUCH better equipment then us Mages. <br>
***<br>
<br>
Uh?<br>
<br>
***<br>
VI. Ok, now what we are asking for and how it will be fair to every class so that it will be reasonable. We are asking for our pets to be buffed up back to the way when they proved to be the best soloing class. Ok, maybe I suppose we can skip them being THE BEST soloing class, but second place to Shaman's wouldn't be bad.<br>
***<br>
<br>
Man, you're confused. You ask for pets to be buffed back &quot;the way when they proved to be the best soloing class&quot;... Do you even realise that YOU ARE AT THAT POINT. When the heck do you think mage were at their top power? PRE-KUNARK, yes that's right, in the 1-50 range, exactly where you are right now... (and the curent end game mage are reaching that same point again, if there's any slow part in the mage leveling curve now, it has to be 50-60 for non-epic mages). As for shaman being the best soloer, that's not true. Shaman will be able to take bigger targets at higher levels, yes. But in 1 hour period a mage chain soloing will kill more and get more xp than a shaman, that's a simple fact. And ya I should know, I don't only have mage and shaman toons, I have epic mage and epic shaman toon. ;P<br>
<br>
Then there's your part about the other classes. Lots of stuff in there is simply not true. Bard melee skills are pathetic at best, they are, by far, the least damaging melee class with their weapons, and by far, your pet should easily outdamage a bard melee unless he is extremely twinked. Monks are not the best damage dealers in game, rogues/mage and later wiz outdamage them. Paladins and SK are awesome in the post 50 game, they are another story before that. It's MUCH easier to level an untwinked mage than an untwinked knight. Rangers are weak soloers at low level, but in later levels, rangers are simply the BEST soloers (good bow + EQ + AM3 + 14 damage arrows = own). etc, etc.<br>
<br>
Sorry but there's no valid reason to sign this.<br>
